TWEET: Monitoring the situation intoxicates you. It degrades your attention and decision making capacity.
REPLY: From a Vedantic lens:
This happens when manas (the reactive mind) keeps looping on the situation. Attention fragments, and buddhi (discernment) loses clarity.
Distance restores buddhi — which is why stepping back improves judgment.

